OL,3,CWhy volunteering is at the heart of
OL,4,Cour communities
OL,6,FSam lives with complex health issues
OL,7,Fand three times a year, he spends time
OL,8,Fat the Children's Hospice. While Sam
OL,9,Fis treated like a prince (Elaine's
OL,10,Fwords), the family gets some down time
OL,11,Fto recharge and regroup.
OL,13,FFor Elaine, like many of us, she
OL,14,Fthought of hospices as places where
OL,15,Fpeople managed the end of life.
OL,17,FShe never anticipated that the hospice
OL,18,Fwould become such a large part of her
OL,19,Ffamily's life.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
