OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1780592748
OL,3,CWhy volunteering is at the heart of
OL,4,Cour communities
OL,6,FShe acknowledges that there is sadness
OL,7,Fin hospices but the ethos of the
OL,8,Forganisation is that even though that
OL,9,Fis the case, that doesn't mean
OL,10,Fpatients and families have to live in
OL,11,Fconstant sadness.
OL,13,FThat happiness and joy can still be
OL,14,Ffound, even temporarily and memories
OL,15,Fcan still be made. Life can still be
OL,16,Flived. And a hospice is a place which
OL,17,Fstrives to provide those moments of
OL,18,Flight.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
